---

Option 1: Use Only ACF

Choose this when the project only needs structured content management.

Best For

- Hero Sections
- FAQs
- Testimonials
- Team Members
- Pricing Tables
- Product Specifications
- Company Information
- Landing Pages
- Galleries
- Contact Information

Characteristics

- Mostly content
- Little or no business logic
- Editors manage everything
- Standard frontend display

Advantages

- Fast development
- Easy for clients
- Little code
- Easy maintenance

---

Option 2: Build a Custom Plugin

Choose this when the project is mainly functionality.

Best For

- WooCommerce Extensions
- Payment Gateways
- License Managers
- Booking Systems
- Membership Systems
- CRM
- Inventory Management
- REST APIs
- Automation
- Security Features

Characteristics

- Heavy business logic
- Custom workflows
- Integrations
- AJAX
- Scheduled Tasks
- Custom Database Tables
- Complex Validation

Advantages

- Full control
- High performance
- No dependency on ACF
- Easier to distribute as a standalone plugin

---

Option 3: Use ACF + Custom Plugin

This is the most common architecture for professional WordPress projects.

ACF Handles

- Admin UI
- Data Entry
- Validation
- Repeaters
- Flexible Content
- Relationships
- Options Pages

Plugin Handles

- Business Logic
- Frontend Rendering
- WooCommerce Integration
- API Calls
- Search & Filtering
- Comparison
- Automation
- Custom Shortcodes
- Gutenberg Blocks
- Widgets

Best For

- Mobile Database
- Real Estate
- Course Websites
- Directories
- Product Catalogs
- Review Websites
- Job Boards

---

When NOT to Use ACF

Avoid ACF if the project requires:

- Highly custom admin dashboards
- Custom database tables
- Thousands of records with performance-critical queries
- Complex workflows
- Heavy AJAX interfaces
- Drag-and-drop builders
- Standalone plugin distribution without dependencies

In these cases, build the admin UI yourself inside the plugin.

---

Quick Decision Checklist

Choose ACF if:

- [ ] The project mainly stores content.
- [ ] Standard field types are sufficient.
- [ ] Editors will manage the data.
- [ ] No complex workflows exist.

---

Choose Plugin if:

- [ ] The project focuses on functionality.
- [ ] Complex business logic is required.
- [ ] Custom database tables are needed.
- [ ] Performance is critical.
- [ ] The plugin should have no dependency on ACF.

---

Choose ACF + Plugin if:

- [ ] The project needs structured content.
- [ ] It also requires custom business logic.
- [ ] Editors should have an easy admin interface.
- [ ] Frontend output is highly customized.
- [ ] Integrations or automation are required.

